\cf3 *** Comments to the authors: Comments to the authors\
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf2 \
The authors propose to represent relational data through graphical models (both for individual items and at the population level). Outlier detection is then posed as a problem of "deviation" of the individual graphical model from the population model. The deviation is quantified through \'a0\'a0\
a metric based on the likelihood ratio of the two parameter vectors.\
\
I think this is a very interesting and well written paper. Of course, other more involved deviation quantifications between distributions represented by the individual and population graphical models can be envisaged, but to be fair, the authors are well aware of this and even go some length in this direction in the experiments.\
\
Nice paper!\
