\cf3 *** Comments to the authors: Comments to the authors\
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf2 \
The contribution deals with the extremely important problem how to detect outliers in relational data bases. The approach follows a probabilistic model which is based on the (pseudo)likelihood of the data. As a novelty, it suggests to take into account class and object likelihood, and it suggests a distance which avoids averaging of differences. One great plus is not only its superior performance, but its interpretability since it provides explicit rankings of factors which contribute to an instance being regarded as outlier.\
\
The proposal is extremely well written as concerns a tutorial character as well as the novel proposal, which is consistently phrased based on fundamental principles from probabilistic modeling. The experiments are accompanied by available data/code, and they are convincing. \
\
An excellent contribution!\
